-0.200 0 (         [Bjarne, core-7290:])A 
; : 161 2009 1850 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2009 M 
-0.200 0 (           It has been a principle throughout that constructed sub-objects)A 
; : 161 2054 1850 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2054 M 
-0.200 0 (           are destroyed if a constructor throws an exception.  Consider a)A 
; : 161 2099 1375 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2099 M 
-0.200 0 (           base an unnamed member and it all works out.)A 
; : 161 2189 875 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2189 M 
-0.200 0 (         [John Skaller, core-7294:])A 
; : 161 2279 1250 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2279 M 
-0.200 0 (           I assume the base destructor IS called.)A 
; : 161 2369 1825 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
161 2369 M 
-0.200 0 (           There are TWO reasons to destroy the object, the first is that)A 
; : 161 2414 1775 45 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji 
